Class SunriseTimeStamp

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.kuka.roboticsAPI.controllerModel.sunrise.SunriseTimeStamp

  • public class SunriseTimeStamp
extends Object
    Timestamp Support Class for interaction to realtime system.

    Timestamps, being computed/sent by realtime system can be converted to java time.

      • toMillis

        public long toMillis()
        Returns the timestamp in milliseconds since January 1, 1970. Note that while the unit of time of the return value is a millisecond, the granularity of the value depends on the underlying operating system and may be larger. For example, many operating systems measure time in units of tens of milliseconds.

        See the description of the class Date for a discussion of slight discrepancies that may arise between "computer time" and coordinated universal time (UTC).

        Returns:
        long - milliseconds between the current time and midnight, January 1, 1970 UTC
        See Also:
        Date
